    "text": "Issue 4: There are four ways of comprehending the opinion of the Jurist and his verdicts:\n• First : Hearing (the verdict) from the Jurist directly or seeing his writing.\n• Second : Seeing his practical report which is possible to rely upon.\n• Third : Hearing from he whose word and report is reliable.\n• Fourth : Notoriety among people in manner obliging dependence and reliability in it."
