    "text": "Issue 192: Haidh is that (bleeding) which may be at times considered as a monthly custom, the blood being discharged from the womb in every month for a number of days, in most cases. This blood is converted to nourishment for the embryo at the time of inception. The woman who is in the state of Haidh is said to be Haa ’ idh . For the Haa’idh in the noble Islamic legislation there are some rules whose mention will come in the following issues."
