    "text": "9. The infant who is born due to its birth.\n10. The Ghusl of a woman who perfumed herself for someone other than her husband and the Ghusl of someone who slept drunken.\n11. Ghusl of someone who went to see the Hanged Person (Masloob) and saw him but if he saw him accidentally or if he went for an important matter like a witness, then there is no Ghusl on his account.\n12. The Ghusl of Taubah, meaning whenever a sin is committed, then, repentance is made and the bath (of repentance) is performed."
