    "text": "Issue 459: The Second Condition : it is to intend from the beginning of the matter to travel the legal distance. Based on this, when one intends from the beginning to travel less than eight Faraasikh and in the way or after arriving to the intended place, one intends to extend his journey so that the total is eight Faraasikh, due to that, he prays a complete prayer and does not shorten it.\nHowever, when it is intended during or after arriving at the intended destination to travel eight Faraasikh or more (further), one's prayer is shortened."
